test.description: The NEO Personality Inventory, authored by Paul T. Costa, Jr. and Robert R. McCrae, is one of the most widely used commercial inventories for measuring the five major domains (and facets of those domains) of personality. Decades of research support the reliability, validity, and utility of the scales of the NEO PI.

traits: an open personality, easy going about life and receptive to new ideas
gives the impression of a carefree and frivolous person
more often trusts his feelings and intuition than common sense
adventurous, eager to get out of their comfort zone and experience something new
wants to break out of a monotonous routine, he likes to approach everything creatively
